<h3>AFFILIATE AGREEMENT</h3>
<div class='agency-signup-terms'>
	<p>THIS AFFILIATE AGREEMENT (the “Agreement”), is made and entered into
by and between The entity that has signed up on this sign up process (hereinafter referred to as “Affiliate”) and Plexuss, Inc., a Delaware corporation (“Plexuss”).  (Affiliate and Plexuss are each a "Party" and collectively, the “Parties”).</p>

	<p class='text-center'><b>RECITALS</b></p>

	<p><b>WHEREAS</b>, both the Affiliate and the University recognize the trend towards international education;</p>

	<p><b>WHEREAS</b>, Plexuss is a recognized leader in international college recruiting and assists domestic colleges and universities in recruiting international students who seek admission to such colleges and universities;</p>

	<p><b>WHEREAS</b>, Plexuss has hundreds of colleges and universities in its network and Plexuss supports these institutions by sourcing qualified international students who may pursue a course of study at such institutions;</p>

	<p><b>WHEREAS</b>, the Affiliate has represented to Plexuss that it has the expertise to recruit individuals in country(s) indicated in the Affiliate’s profile (the “Territory”);</p> 

	<p><b>WHEREAS</b>, Plexuss wishes to contract with Affiliate for the provision of certain services relating to the recruitment of individuals (the “Services”) in the Territory. For further clarity, this Agreement shall apply to the recruitment of students in the Territory for degree programs offered by schools affiliated with Plexuss.</p> 

	<p><b>NOW THEREFORE</b>, in consideration of the mutual covenants herein contained, the Parties hereto agree as follows:</p>

	<p><b>I. DEFINITIONS</b></p>
	<p>In addition to terms defined elsewhere herein, the following terms have the following meanings when used in this Agreement:</p>

	<p><b>“Territory”</b> shall be defined as the country, area or region in which the agent operates and has a physical presence (such as an office).  The Territory governed by this specific agreement shall be in country(s) indicated in the Affiliate’s profile.</p>

	<p><b>“Plexuss Platform”</b> shall be defined as the proprietary software-as-a-service product of Plexuss.</p>

	<p><b>“Plexuss Network Schools”</b> shall be defined as the colleges and universities based in the United States with whom Plexuss has contracted and on behalf of whom Plexuss is recruiting international students for matriculation.</p> 

	<p><b>“Affiliate”</b> shall be defined as the marketing representative with whom Plexuss is contracting by way of this Agreement.</p> 

	<p><b>“Confidential Information”</b> includes, to the extent allowed by law, any and all of the following information of any Party that has been or may hereafter be disclosed in any form, whether in writing, orally, electronically or otherwise, or otherwise made available by observation, inspection or otherwise by any Party or its employees, agents, contractors, or representatives (collectively, a “Disclosing Party”) to another party or its employees, agents, contractors or representatives (collectively, a “Receiving Party”):</p>
	<ul style="list-style: none;">
		<li>(i) all information that is a trade secret under applicable trade secret or other law;</li>
		<li>(ii) all information concerning product specifications, data, know-how, formulae, compositions, processes, designs, sketches, photographs, graphs, drawings, samples, inventions and ideas, past, current and planned research and development, current and planned manufacturing or distribution methods and processes, customer lists, current and anticipated customer requirements, price lists, market studies, business plans, computer hardware, software and computer software and database technologies, systems, structures and architectures;</li>
		<li>(iii) all information concerning the business and affairs of the Disclosing Party (which includes historical and current financial statements, financial projections and budgets, tax returns and accountants’ materials, historical, current and projected sales, capital spending budgets and plans, business plans, strategic plans, marketing and advertising plans, publications, client and customer lists and files, contracts, the names and backgrounds of key personnel and personnel training techniques and materials, however documented), and all information obtained from review of the Disclosing Party’s documents or property or discussions with the Disclosing Party regardless of the form of the communication; and</li>
		<li>(iv) all notes, analyses, compilations, studies, summaries and other material prepared by the Receiving Party to the extent containing or based, in whole or in part, upon any information included in the foregoing.</li>
	</ul>

	<p><b>II. PURPOSE; APPOINTMENT OF AFFILIATE</b></p>

	<p>Plexuss would like to make the credit programs of study of the educational institutions in its network known and available to potential students in Affiliate’s Territory.  To further that goal, 
		Plexuss hereby appoints the Affiliate as its exclusive marketing representative to assist Plexuss in marketing and promotion in Affiliate’s Territory. Affiliate hereby agrees to act in that capacity subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement.</p>

	<p><b>III. PLEXUSS RESPONSIBILITIES</b></p>

	<p>Plexuss will assume the following responsibilities:</p>

	<ul style="list-style: none;">
		<li>A. Grant to Affiliate the exclusive right to represent Plexuss and certain of the Plexuss Network Schools for the purposes of: (1) disseminating information about the college and its programs in Affiliate’s Territory; (2) screening and recommending prospective students in the Territory to Plexuss; and 3) assisting students in the Territory with applying to Plexuss Network Schools by way of the Plexuss platform.</li>

		<li>B. Provide Affiliate with up-to-date written and/or electronic materials, website links and other sources that include information on admissions criteria, processes, procedures and documents necessary for the application process; tuition & fees; academic programs; academic calendar; location; facilities, including accommodations; meal plans; etc.</li>

		<li>C. Provide Affiliate with access to the Plexuss Platform, including access to Plexuss’ OneApp product for student applications. Plexuss will also provide Affiliate with detailed contact information on students in Affiliate’s Territory by way of the Plexuss Platform. The Plexuss Platform will provide Affiliate with features including applicant tracking and detailed applicant contact information in the Affiliate’s Territory.</li>

		<li>D. Respond in a reasonable response time to Affiliate inquiries and processing of Affiliate student applications.</li>

		<li>E. Pay an Affiliate commission as outlined herein, subject to the terms set forth herein.</li>

		<li>F. Endeavor to waive the application fee for a student applying to up to ten colleges or universities by way of the Plexuss platform.</li>

		<li>G. Appoint a liaison responsible for all matters concerning the agreement, including communication between Plexuss and Affiliate. This Agreement and any obligations hereunder may not be assigned or delegated to a third party.</li>

		<li>H. Plexuss will endeavor to provide certain post-admission services for students recruited by Affiliate including, but not limited to, concierge services, off-campus housing and job placement and internship placement services.</li>
	</ul>

	<p><b>AFFILIATE RESPONSIBILITIES AND AUTHORITY</b></p>
	<p>The broad responsibilities and authority of Affiliate are as follows:</p>

	<ul style="list-style: none;">

		<li>A. Distribute written materials to prospective applicants in the Territory which include clear statements regarding Affiliate’s services; fee structure, including what is/is not included in agency fees and processing/handling fees; refund policy, including dates for calculating refunds; and guarantees, including what the agency can/cannot guarantee, before students enroll in Affiliate services. The Affiliate will take reasonable measures necessary for prospective applicants to understand and acknowledge the nature of the relationship between Affiliate and Plexuss. Affiliate agrees to provide any published material that references Plexuss and/or its network institutions to Plexuss for review and approval.</li>

    	<li>B. Affiliate will evaluate and screen all prospective students in its Territory and recommended for admission to a Plexuss Network School regarding academic ability, financial ability, and other criteria as directed by Plexuss.</li>

     	<li>C. Place or attempt to place with Plexuss Network Schools those students who Affiliate originally identifies in its Territory via the Plexuss Platform.</li>

     	<li>D. Place or attempt to place with Plexuss Network Schools those students who Affiliate originally identifies in its Territory by means other than the Plexuss Platform.</li>

  		<li>E. Promote and publicize educational opportunities at Plexuss Network Schools to ensure that the quality and value of attending Plexuss Network Schools are widely advertised to prospective applicants who have the necessary educational background, intellectual capacity, and motivation to succeed as students at Plexuss Network Schools.</li>

    	<li>F. Recruit nonresident, international applicants for enrollment at Plexuss Network Schools consistent with Plexuss Network Schools’ undergraduate and graduate admissions requirements, academic guidelines and policies, and immigration requirements of the United States. Such recruitment activity will not include students who would otherwise have attended or were contacted first by another entity besides Affiliate.</li>

     	<li>G. Distribute written and/or electronic materials provided by Plexuss Network Schools to prospective applicants which include information on admissions criteria, processes, procedures and documents necessary for the application process; academic programs; academic calendar; location; facilities, including accommodations; meal plans; etc.</li>

     	<li>H. Distribute written and/or electronic materials to prospective applicants which include an itemized list of tuition and fees associated with attendance at Plexuss Network Schools, always shown in USD, which makes clear that the only official tuition and fee amounts are on the Plexuss Network Schools’ or Plexuss’ website.</li>

    	<li>I. Offer services related to application to Plexuss Network Schools, including one-on-one counseling, arranging interviews with Plexuss Network Schools or Plexuss representatives visiting Affiliate facilities, assisting applicants throughout the OneApp application process, assisting applicants with visa applications, and additional follow-up services.</li>

     	<li>J. Assist students with completing applications on the OneApp platform by the application deadline. 

    	<li>K. Deliver to Plexuss a minimum of twenty (20) completed student applications per month.

     	<li>L. Provide guidance on cultural differences, differences between the American and home country university systems, and social acclimation while recruiting the student and facilitating the student/university match in coordination with resources provided by the Plexuss Network Schools or Plexuss liaison.</li>

     	<li>M. Inform Plexuss when each student receives a visa. Assist the student with travel arrangements and logistics and inform Plexuss of students’ arrival plans no less than one week from arrival date.</li>

     	<li>N. Ensure that all written materials meet marketing and branding requirements of Plexuss Network Schools and policies and procedures of Plexuss Network Schools. These materials must be approved through the Plexuss liaison prior to publication, online or in print.</li>

    	<li>O. Affiliate agrees to keep and maintain all student related information and records in accordance with U.S. law, including Federal Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA) and to obtain any necessary releases for disclosure of student information regarding admitted and matriculated students.</li>

     	<li>P. Affiliate agrees to conduct student recruitment, marketing and development of educational projects together with Plexuss.</li>

     	<li>Q. Affiliate agrees that Plexuss reserves the right to refer to Affiliate as a “partner”, “affiliate”, “associate” and/or similar term in order to acknowledge its marketing relationship with Affiliate.</li>

     	<li>R. Affiliate agrees to use Plexuss marketing material and/or trade dress in its offices in the Territory in order to clearly demonstrate an affiliation with Plexuss.</li>

     	<li>S. Affiliate agrees to respond to an “in-Territory” student inquiry within 48 hours of such inquiry.</li>

     	<li>T. Affiliate agrees to, at all times, conduct themselves in a professional manner as a representative of Plexuss.</li>

     	<li>U. Affiliate will clearly indicate on the OneApp application that the student is referred by Affiliate. The relevant Plexuss Network School reserves the sole right and responsibility for official admission decisions and notification.</li>

     	<li>V. Affiliate agrees to take necessary steps to increase awareness in the local community about Plexuss and Plexuss Network Schools.</li>

     	<li>W. Prior to execution of this Agreement, Affiliate agrees to provide Plexuss with a list of colleges and universities on whose behalf Affiliate is currently providing services similar to the Services described in this Agreement.</li>

     	<li>X. Assisting Plexuss Network Schools faculty and staff – and/or Plexuss team members -  who might visit Affiliate’s region for recruitment efforts.</li>

     	<p><b>V. AFFILIATE PROHIBITED ACTIVITY</b></p>

     	<p>Affiliate shall not:</p>
		
		<ul style="list-style: none;">

	     	<li>A. Make any representations or offer any guarantees or promises to prospective students about specific courses, programs, or majors they will be able to take or enroll in, or scholarships or financial assistance.</li>

	    	<li>B. Accept payments from students on behalf of Plexuss, a Plexuss Network School or otherwise. Students shall make all payments for the costs of attendance directly to Plexuss or the Plexuss Network School.</li>

			<li>C. Make any overt or implied claim or representation, or offer any guarantees or promises, to prospective students with respect to individual employment following the completion of any of the Plexuss Network School’s educational programs.</li>

			<li>D. Contest admission decisions or placement recommendations into degree-programs by a Plexuss Network School.</li>

			<li>E. Place or attempt to place a student sourced from the Plexuss Platform with a non- Plexuss Network School without Plexuss’ prior, express written consent.</li>

			<li>F. Work directly with or otherwise directly engage a Plexuss Network School.</li>

		</ul>

		<p><b>VI. PAYMENT TERMS</b></p>

		<p></p>

		<ul style="list-style: none;">
			<li>A. Plexuss shall compensate Affiliate according to the progressive fee schedule attached hereto as Exhibit “A”.</li>
			
			<li>B. In the Fall of each year, Plexuss will compensate Affiliate for each individual student that the Affiliate has assisted, provided orientation to, and recommended for admission to a Plexuss Network School if the student: (1) is admitted; (2) pays tuition due; and (3) attends classes for at least thirty-five calendar days from the beginning of the quarter or semester.  The date of Plexuss’ Fall payment to Affiliate will vary depending on the academic calendar for the relevant Plexuss Network School for which Affiliate has sourced an enrollee. Plexuss will compensate Affiliate only with respect to students whom or for whom Affiliate has oriented, evaluated, screened, facilitated the application process, and recommended for admission.</li>

			<li>C. Plexuss will not pay any fees to Affiliate for students that withdraw from a Plexuss Network School prior to the thirty-fifth calendar day of the quarter or semester.</li>

			<li>D. The Affiliate shall provide satisfactory invoices and original supporting documentation to Plexuss in a form as set out in Exhibit "B".</li>

			<li>E. The Affiliate is solely responsible for making any arrangements and for paying any and all expenses incurred in connection with providing the services (including, without limitation, expenses relating to space, facilities, equipment, materials, telephone, office supplies, document copying, facsimile transmission and postage).</li>
		</ul>

		<p><b>VII. TERMINATION</b></p>
		<ul style="list-style: none;">
			<li>A. <u>Notice.</u> Either party, in its sole discretion, may terminate this agreement by providing the other party thirty (30) days written notice of intent to terminate. All notices are to be hand delivered by duly authorized representatives or mailed through a recognized commercial service.</li>
			
			<li>B. <u>Effect of Termination.</u>  Upon termination of this Agreement for any reason:

				<ul style="list-style: none;">
   					<li>i. outstanding fees earned prior to termination and due to any Party shall become immediately due and payable. Affiliate acknowledges that in the event of a termination by either party, Affiliate shall only be entitled to fees earned up to the termination date.  Plexuss is only obligated to make progressive fee payments to Affiliate during the Term of the Agreement.</li>

					<li>ii. all student data, files and marketing materials shall be transferred from Affiliate to Plexuss;</li>

  					<li>iii. all Confidential Information, including any commercially sensitive information, and any copies thereof, shall be returned to the disclosing party.</li>
				</ul>
			</li>
		</ul>

		<p><b>VIII. REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES</b></p>
		<ul style="list-style: none;">
			<li>A. <u>Authorization, Execution, and Delivery of Agreement.</u> Each Party individually represents and warrants that this Agreement has been duly authorized, executed and delivered by the Party and constitutes the valid and binding obligation of the Party, enforceable in accordance with its terms, except as such enforceability may be limited by applicable bankruptcy, insolvency, moratorium, reorganization or similar laws in effect which affect the enforcement of creditors’ rights generally, by equitable limitations on the availability of specific remedies and by principles of equity.</li>

			<li>B. <u>No Conflict with other Agreements.</u> Each Party individually represents and warrants that the execution, delivery and performance by the Party of this Agreement does not and shall not conflict with, violate, cause a breach of or constitute a default under any material agreement, contract, instrument, order, judgment, decree, law, rule or regulation to which the Party is a party or is subject, except such agreements, contracts and instruments, if any, under which all waivers, consents and approvals that are necessary or required in order to prevent such conflict, violation or breach have been duly and validly obtained by the Party.</li>

			<li>C. <u>Affiliate Authorization.</u> Affiliate has the authority and legal capacity to execute and deliver this Agreement and to perform its obligations hereunder.</li>

			<li>D. <u>Personal Information.</u> Both parties acknowledge that they are subject to educational institution internal policies, laws and regulations that govern and restrict the collection, storage, processing, dissemination and use of non-public personal information that relates to applicants to an educational institution as well as to educational institution students and personnel and that could be used, either directly or indirectly, to identify such person (collectively, “Personal Information”). Plexuss and Affiliate further acknowledges that during the course of its recruitment of, and application processing for, prospective students, Plexuss and Affiliate shall gain access to Personal Information. Plexuss and Affiliate shall, and shall cause its employees, agents, servants, principals, and any subcontractors to, at all times comply with all applicable laws, rules, regulations and Plexuss Network School policies, including privacy and information security laws and regulations and Plexuss Network School policies regarding Personal Information relating to the performance of Plexuss’ and Affiliate’s obligations under this Agreement. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, Plexuss and Affiliate agree (a) not to collect, store, process, disseminate, or use any such Personal Information obtained from Plexuss Network Schools except to the extent expressly permitted or required in the performance of its obligations under this Agreement, (b) to store all such Personal Information only in encrypted or otherwise secure form on Plexuss’ network and (c) not to sell, distribute, release or disclose lists or compilations of any items of Personal Information without the prior written consent of Plexuss Network Schools or of the subject(s) of the Personal Information to be released or disclosed.  Any disclosure of Personal Information by Plexuss or Affiliate in the performance of its obligations hereunder shall be made only on a “need-to-know” basis and subject to an applicable confidentiality agreement or other obligation substantially similar to the confidentiality, privacy and information security requirements imposed on Plexuss under this Agreement and applicable law.</li>

			<li>E. <u>Student Privacy Rights.</u>  Without limitation of its obligations under Section VIII A above, (a) Plexuss and Affiliate shall take all commercially reasonable measures to protect the Personal Information of University students consistent with Family Education Rights and Privacy Act (“FERPA”) and the applicable laws of the State of California, (b) Plexuss shall furnish University a copy of Plexuss’ information security procedures for the storage and handling of education records and other Personal Information prior to the commencement of Plexuss’ handling and processing of such matter, (c) Plexuss shall furnish University a copy of any update or other modification of such security procedures and (d) such security procedures and all updates and modifications thereof shall be subject to University’s written approval.</li>

			<li>F. <u>Academic Matters.</u>  The parties acknowledge that all decisions whether to admit, enroll, or matriculate any applicant is solely subject to the discretion of the relevant Plexuss Network School.  The Plexuss Network School will evaluate all undergraduate and graduate program applicants who submit complete applications to consider whether they meet Plexuss Network School’s admission requirements, comply with Plexuss Network School’s timelines and requirements, and the immigration requirements of the United States. The Plexuss Network School reserves the right to limit the number of admitted students referred by Affiliate based on such factors as available funding for commissions, geographical area saturation, program capacity, and total international student enrollment projections.</li>

    		<li>G. <u>Recruitment Efforts.</u>  Affiliate acknowledges that all of its recruiting activities shall relate solely to the recruitment of foreign students residing in foreign countries who are not eligible to receive United States Federal student assistance.</li>

    		<li>H. <u>Capacity.</u>  Affiliate represents to Plexuss that Affiliate has sufficient staff available to provide the services to be delivered under this Agreement and that all individuals providing such services have the background, training, and experience to provide the services to be delivered to Plexuss under this Agreement.</li>

			<li>I. <u>Compliance.</u>  Affiliate represents that it shall comply, at its sole cost and expense, with all laws, codes, regulations, registration, licensing and permit requirements of all governments and governmental authorities, applicable to its activities in connection with this Agreement, including but not limited to those of the European Union or other multistate regional authorities.  Upon execution of this Agreement, Affiliate shall provide, in a form acceptable to Plexuss, evidence of its compliance with all such registration, licensing and permit requirements.</li> 

			<li>J. <u>Plexuss Property.</u>  Affiliate represents that any materials provided by Plexuss to Affiliate for use in the provision of the services under this Agreement shall remain the property of Plexuss and shall be returned without cost to Plexuss upon request.</li>

    		<li>K. <u>School Intellectual Property.</u>  Affiliate shall not use the name, trademarks, logotypes, or related indicia of any Plexuss Network School in any publication, advertisement, or news release without prior approval of an authorized official of Plexuss.  Any copyrights or publication rights arising from or relative to materials developed by Plexuss and/or a Plexuss Network School in connection with this agreement belong exclusively to Plexuss and/or a Plexuss Network School.</li> 

			<li>L. <u>Insurance.</u>  Affiliate shall carry liability insurance that covers all third-party claims against the vendor and/or Plexuss that may arise from Affiliate activities under this agreement.  Said insurance shall be in an amount equivalent to one million United States dollars (US $1,000,000.00).</li>

			<li>M. <u>Indemnification.</u>  Affiliate agrees to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless Plexuss, its successors and assigns, and their respective employees and agents to the fullest extent permitted by law from and against any and all claims or demands whatsoever, including associated costs, expenses, and reasonable attorneys’ fees incurred on account thereof, that may be asserted by Affiliate’s employees, employees of Affiliate’s subcontractors or agents, or any other persons for loss, damage, death, or injury to persons or property arising in any manner out of or incident to Affiliate’s performance or nonperformance of this Agreement.</li>

		</ul>

		<p><b>IX. TERM AND EXCLUSIVITY</b></p>

		<ul style="list-style: none;">
			<li>A. <u>Term.</u> This Agreement shall begin on the Effective Date and shall, unless terminated sooner in accordance with other provisions of this Agreement, expire on the five (5)-year anniversary of the Effective Date (the “Initial Term,” collectively with any Renewal Terms, the “Term”). If not sooner terminated, the Parties may elect, no later than one hundred eighty (180) days prior to the expiration of the Initial Term, by their prior written mutual consent, duly authorized by all Parties, to renew this Agreement for one additional five (5)-year period (the “Renewal Term”).</li>

			<li>B. Plexuss Exclusivity.</u> During the Term, Affiliate shall not, either independently or in conjunction with any person, whether directly or indirectly, participate in any international recruiting program with a competitor of Plexuss where such participation would involve services that are substantially similar to the ones memorialized in this Agreement.  In addition, Affiliate shall not, either independently or in conjunction with any person, whether directly or indirectly, participate in any international recruiting program directly with a Plexuss Network School.  In the event Affiliate breaches this clause, Plexuss shall: a) not be obligated to compensate Affiliate for services provided to Affiliate under this Agreement prior to the breach; and b) have the right to terminate this Agreement immediately.</li>

			<li>C. Leads and Application. Affiliate must deliver 20 completed and Plexuss verified applications before receiving leads from Plexuss. Plexuss will provide a unique application link to the Affiliate. Application will require verified information such as back statements, transcripts and others. Plexuss reserved the right to reject incomplete and falsied applications. Leads are defined as students who have registered on Plexuss and are in Affiliate’s region.</li>

			<li>D. Affiliate Exclusivity. Affiliate shall be considered Plexuss’ exclusive representative in the Territory when the Affiliate delivers a minimum of 50 enrolled students to Plexuss Network Schools year during a year. Plexuss shall be responsible for tracking enrolled students sourced by Affiliate and shall monitor such enrollments on a quarterly basis.</li>
		</ul>

		<p><b>X. MISCELLANEOUS</b></p>
		<ul style="list-style: none;">
			<li><u>A. Independent Contractor Relationship.</u> Affiliate’s relationship with Plexuss is that of an independent contractor, and nothing in this Agreement is intended to, or should be construed to, create a partnership, agency, joint venture or employment relationship.  Affiliate is not authorized to make any representation, contract or commitment on behalf of Plexuss unless specifically requested or authorized in writing to do so by an officer of Plexuss.  Affiliate is solely responsible for, and will file, on a timely basis, all tax returns and payments required to be filed with, or made to, any federal, state or local tax authority with respect to the performance of services and receipt of fees under this Agreement. Affiliate is solely responsible for, and must maintain adequate records of, expenses incurred in the course of performing services under this Agreement.</li>

			<li><u>B. Successors and Assigns.</u>  Each and all of the covenants, terms, provisions, and agreements contained in this Agreement shall be binding upon and inure to the benefit of the Parties hereto and, to the extent permitted by this Agreement, their respective successors and assigns. No Party may assign this Agreement (by operation of law or otherwise) to any other party (individual or entity) without the prior written consent of the other Party.</li>

			<li><u>Confidentiality.</u> The following terms governing confidentiality shall apply:</li>
			<ul style="list-style: none;">

				<li>i. <u>Restricted Use of Confidential Information.</u> Each Receiving Party acknowledges the confidential and proprietary nature of the Confidential Information of the Disclosing Party and agrees that such Confidential Information to the extent allowed by law (i) shall be kept confidential by the Receiving Party; (ii) shall not be used for any reason or purpose other than to perform services in connection with this Agreement; and (iii) without limiting the foregoing, shall not be disclosed by the Receiving Party to any person or entity, except in each case as otherwise expressly permitted by the terms of this Agreement or with the prior written consent of an authorized representative of the Disclosing Party.</li>

				<li>ii. <u>Exceptions.</u> Subsection A above does not apply to that part of the Confidential Information of a Disclosing Party that a Receiving Party demonstrates (i) was, is, or becomes generally available to the public other than as a result of a breach of Subsection A above by the Receiving Party or its representatives; (ii) was or is developed by the Receiving Party independently of and without reference to any Confidential Information of the Disclosing Party; or (iii) was, is, or becomes available to the Receiving Party on a non-confidential basis from a third party not bound by a confidentiality agreement or any legal, fiduciary or other obligation restricting disclosure.</li>

 				<li>iii. <u>Return or Destruction of Confidential Information.</u> Except as otherwise required by this Agreement and/or applicable law, upon the expiration or termination of this Agreement, each Receiving Party shall, to the extent allowed by law, (i) destroy all Confidential Information of the Disclosing Party prepared or generated by the Receiving Party without retaining a copy of any such material; and (ii) promptly deliver to the Disclosing Party all other Confidential Information of the Disclosing Party, together with  all copies thereof, in the possession, custody or control of the Receiving Party or, alternatively, with the written consent of the Disclosing Party, destroy all such Confidential Information.</li>

 				<li>iv. <u>Attorney-Client Privilege.</u> The Disclosing Party is not waiving, and will not be deemed to have waived or diminished, and no Receiving Party will claim or contend  that any Disclosing Party has waived, any of its attorney work-product protections, attorney-client privileges, or similar protections and privileges as a result of disclosing its Confidential Information (including Confidential Information related to pending or threatened litigation) to the Receiving Party, regardless of whether the Disclosing Party has asserted, or is or may be entitled to assert, such privileges and protections.</li>
		</ul>
		<li>D. <u>Dispute Resolution.</u> Any dispute relating to this Agreement; the making, performance, nonperformance or termination of this Agreement; or any transaction in connection with this Agreement shall be resolved in the following manner: The parties shall first meet in good faith and attempt to resolve the dispute on their own.  If the dispute cannot be resolved by the parties, the dispute shall be submitted to arbitration. Such arbitration shall be conducted in San Francisco, California in accordance with the rules of the American Arbitration Association (“AAA”). The award of such arbitration shall be final, binding and non-appealable, except to the extent provided for in the rules of the AAA.  The arbitrator(s) may not amend or alter any term of this Agreement, shall apply the law as set forth herein, and shall have the discretion to impose the cost of the arbitration upon the losing party or divide it between the parties upon any terms which (s)he/they deem appropriate; provided, however, that each party shall bear its own legal fees and costs.  A judgment upon an award rendered by the arbitrator(s) may be entered in any court of competent jurisdiction, or application may be made to such court for confirmation of such award or a judicial acceptance of such award, and for an order of enforcement or other legal remedy.</li>

		<li>E. <u>FERPA Obligations.</u> The Parties shall maintain all educational records and information concerning all international students recruited by Plexuss (“Educational Records”) consistent with the University’s policies, the Family Education Rights and Privacy Act (“FERPA”), and all applicable laws. All Educational Records shall be and remain the property of the University. The Parties acknowledge that, in order to carry out the Public Purpose of this Agreement, the University is outsourcing to Plexuss certain institutional services and functions for which the University would otherwise use its own employees; that Plexuss is under the University’s direct control with respect to the use and maintenance of the Educational Records; that Plexuss will use the Educational Records only for the purpose for which the disclosure was made; and that Plexuss may have access to all Educational Records relevant to the scope of the services necessary to carry out their obligations under this Agreement strictly in accordance with 34 C.F.R. 99.31(a)(1)(B) and 99.33(a). The University acknowledges that Plexuss has legitimate educational interests in access to Educational Records because such access is relevant and necessary to carry out the Public Purpose, services, and functions under this Agreement and that such access shall be subject to and limited by 34 C.F.R. 99.31(a)(1)(B) and 99.33(a). To the extent Plexuss utilizes subcontractors, Plexuss shall require each such subcontractors to agree in writing to terms substantively similar to the obligations in this Section. Plexuss and any of its contractors will not disclose or release Educational Records without the prior written consent of the University and, as applicable, the parent or the affected student(s), except as required by judicial order or lawfully issued subpoena. Plexuss shall immediately report to the University any unauthorized use or disclosure of records or information used or maintained by Plexuss that are protected by law or the terms of this Agreement, including FERPA or state consumer and/or data protection laws, once Plexuss becomes aware of such unauthorized use or disclosure. Plexuss shall cooperate with the University to send any notice the University believes is necessary to individuals whose information may have been used or breached as described herein.</li>

